{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:08:31.523088+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: b31dcaee641dae642e277a9d9dd36222f3ddc362)", "id": "lc_3cecb709-887b-4c99-8bc1-294c251c39e0"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Thin wrappers around git subprocess calls used by gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\n\n\ndef _git(*args: str) -> str:\n    return subprocess.check_output([\"git\", *args], text=True).strip()\n\n\ndef status_summary() -> str:\n    branch = _git(\"rev-parse\", \"--abbrev-ref\", \"HEAD\")\n    try:\n        upstream = _git(\"rev-parse\", \"--abbrev-ref\", f\"{branch}@{{upstream}}\")\n        ahead_behind = _git(\"rev-list\", \"--left-right\", \"--count\", f\"{upstream}...{branch}\")\n        behind, ahead = ahead_behind.split()\n        tracking = f\"(ahead {ahead}, behind {behind})\"\n    except subprocess.CalledProcessError:\n        tracking = \"(no upstream)\"\n\n    porcelain = _git(\"status\", \"--porcelain\").splitlines()\n    staged = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line and line[0] != \" \" and line[0] != \"?\")\n    unstaged = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line and line[1] != \" \")\n    untracked = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line.startswith(\"??\"))\n    return f\"{branch}  {tracking}  staged={staged} unstaged={unstaged} untracked={untracked}\"\n\n\ndef list_merged_branches(protected: list[str]) -> list[str]:\n    out = _git(\"branch\", \"--merged\", \"main\")\n    branches = [line.strip().lstrip(\"* \").strip() for line in out.splitlines()]\n    return [b for b in branches if b and b not in protected]\n\n\ndef delete_branch(name: str) -> None:\n    subprocess.check_call([\"git\", \"branch\", \"-d\", name])\n", "id": "lc_4ab5dafe-3808-4ec5-91df-ffae32a1264a"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "d531c73f-6527-4ad8-8cd4-9286e98f6a5a", "tool_call_id": "call_00_U0xJpUrVRTsYXPfGo91O5631", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:08:36.719959+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Answer\n\nThe package installs a command-line tool called **`gwc`** (Git Workflow Companion).\n\n**What `gwc` does:** It provides opinionated, local-only Git shortcuts for solo developers. It explicitly avoids network operations (push, pull, fetch, clone), rebasing, and credential management.\n\nCurrently, `gwc` exposes three subcommands:\n\n| Subcommand | Behavior |\n|---|---|\n| `gwc status-summary` | Prints a one-line summary of the current branch: branch name, ahead/behind count vs. upstream (if any), and counts of staged, unstaged, and untracked files. |\n| `gwc branch-name <issue-number> <short-slug>` | Generates a conventional branch name (e.g., `issue-42-add-login`) and prints it to stdout. Does not create the branch. |\n| `gwc clean-merged` | Lists local branches fully merged into `main` (default dry-run). With `--apply`, it actually deletes them. Protected branches (configurable via `.gwcrc`) are excluded. |\n\n**Evidence:**\n- **`pyproject.toml`** declares `[project.scripts] gwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"` — the entry point.\n- **`src/gwc/cli.py`** registers the three subparsers (`status-summary`, `branch-name`, `clean-merged`) and dispatches them in `main()`.\n- **`README.md`** documents the same three commands with examples.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 387, "prompt_tokens": 7070, "total_tokens": 7457, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 63, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 6528}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 6528, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 542}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "0748cd10-d6b4-41ec-a4c8-34256bc75e6c", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea421-6123-7533-a343-746caee85ef2-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7070, "output_tokens": 387, "total_tokens": 7457, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 6528}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 63}}}}]}}}
